# Netlify _redirects for Presuntinho V5.
#
# Order matters: Netlify processes rules top-to-bottom, first match wins.
# 1. Static assets are served from the publish directory with their
#    correct Content-Type (no rewrite).  These files exist on disk in
#    `build/` so the SPA fallback rule below must NOT swallow them.
# 2. Everything else (SvelteKit client-side routes) falls through to
#    `index.html` with a 200 (SPA shell).  The SvelteKit client router
#    then takes over and renders the matching route.
#
# Why we keep static-first explicit rules: the Netlify wildcard fallback
# `/* /index.html 200` would otherwise rewrite /sw.js, /robots.txt,
# /sitemap.xml, /manifest.webmanifest, /icons/*.png and every /legacy/
# asset as HTML — which we explicitly verified broke PWA install + SEO.

# --- Static assets (skip SPA fallback) ---

/robots.txt            /robots.txt            200
/sitemap.xml           /sitemap.xml           200
/sw.js                 /sw.js                 200
/manifest.webmanifest  /manifest.webmanifest  200
/favicon.svg           /favicon.svg           200
/favicon-32.png        /favicon-32.png        200
/favicon.ico           /favicon.ico           200
/apple-touch-icon.png  /apple-touch-icon.png  200
/workbox-*.js          /workbox-:splat        200
/icons/*               /icons/:splat          200
/legacy/*              /legacy/:splat         200
/quizzes/*             /quizzes/:splat        200
/lessons/*             /lessons/:splat        200
/auth/*                /auth/:splat           200
/data/*                /data/:splat           200

# --- SPA fallback (everything else) ---

/*                     /index.html            200
